&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adult Psychotherapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Service / Directorate / Specialty&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;South Gloucestershire Psychological Therapies Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base / Location &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kingswood Civic Centre (although clinical sessions may be provided from other South Glos sites).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours / Sessions / PAs / Full Time / Part Time &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;18.75 hrs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type of Contract – Substantive or Fixed Term Tenure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Substantive&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Role and Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;South Gloucestershire is a semi rural area just north of Bristol, with Recovery Team bases in Thornbury and at Kingswood Civic Centre. The post holder will work as a member of the multidisciplinary Psychological Therapies Team (PTS), based Kingswood Civic Centre. The PTS receives approximately two hundred referrals per year from other locality teams. The team is well established and supportive with good relationships with the other teams in the area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder may be required to work in other locations within the locality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The PTS offers a range of therapies for adults with complex mental health difficulties and the post holder will work within the Psychodynamic Psychotherapy work stream. Additionally the post holder will apply their psychological knowledge and skills in a variety of ways within PTS and the wider service (e.g. through consultation, training, supervision, etc). The role will also involve liaison with other parts of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for somebody with excellent communication and engagement skills, who can work autonomously whilst enjoying being an integrated member of the PTS and locality teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills, Experience and Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have a degree and masters level qualification, or equivalent experience and be qualified as an adult psychotherapist, or working towards such qualification, at an accredited training institution. They will also be registered with a relevant professional body, such as UKCP or HCPC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Significant experience of working psychodynamically with patients is essential to the role, as is experience of working within NHS secondary mental health services including knowledge and experience of the role of Care Coordinator and practicing within the CPA model of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits and Opportunities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;South Gloucestershire PTS is a well established and supportive service with excellent relationships across teams. The post holder would have access to specialist supervision and career development via the appraisal process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For Further Information &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information regarding this position, or to arrange a personal visit, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen Young, Team Manager, South Glos Psychological Therapies Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;helen.young@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
